snippet.textDisplay: Eugene finally opened up about something. Tbh, it crosses my mind at time if.... U know... Eugene MIGHT get affected by hate but... at times I was sure of it that he does and I’m not even shocked because I kinda find a lot of things common between the both of us and I personally think that this feeling of.....when u like, you have to be the ‘hardcore’ but u still have that sensitive spot deep in there, it’s kind a one of those common things we both might have... not sure though. Plus, the fact that Eugene’s sexuality is different make NO difference of who he is and well, u should respect that. If u wanna be a nice person, u should respect everyone’s decisions in life. I think all of the Try guys are just imperfectly perfect and they’re SO different from each other that it makes them a perfect group. All of them deserves everything! Of course, being famous u need to be mentally prepared for hate too but it’s not easy to like, BARE the hate especially when u know u r representing like, a hundreds of ppl in Eugenes case. In short, I totally think that everyone have their own ways in life and if everyone starts to think that no one is wrong but they’re just DIFFERENT, I think it can make everyone better in today’s society. Another thing is that as Eugene is a Korean, we’ll, (I’m really not sure about this detail but I’ve heard of it so if I’m wrong pls lemme know) I think it’s like, kind of a disgrace for Korean people do be like.... Gay? Like I said, I HEARD of it, I’m NOT believing it YET but it will be cool if u guys lemme know if it’s true bcoz Koreans are people with high reputation so..... Anyways, I love all of em and I know they HAVE to be my favourite YouTubers. I don’t only love them for the content they make, i dunno them personally but I do love them individually for who they actually are and their personality. U guys really make me smile. Love u all a lot! 🖤🖤

snippet.textDisplay: I think the answer to "no" on "would you accept a 5th Try Guy" lacked a pretty important explanation: they're all really close friends, and that's what makes them have chemistry. They all poked at the notion, but I think the most blunt answer there is that for the guys who answered more on the no side, it was because the show is an integral part of their friendship, rather than the other way around. Inviting another guy in would be easy if they were looking at the show as just an online show separate from their friendship, or at their friendship as being within the confines of the show. It'd be much harder if the show felt to them much more like a personal thing they were supposed to share only with their best friends, and I think that is, to a couple of them at the very least, what the show has become.
snippet.textOriginal: I think the answer to "no" on "would you accept a 5th Try Guy" lacked a pretty important explanation: they're all really close friends, and that's what makes them have chemistry. They all poked at the notion, but I think the most blunt answer there is that for the guys who answered more on the no side, it was because the show is an integral part of their friendship, rather than the other way around. Inviting another guy in would be easy if they were looking at the show as just an online show separate from their friendship, or at their friendship as being within the confines of the show. It'd be much harder if the show felt to them much more like a personal thing they were supposed to share only with their best friends, and I think that is, to a couple of them at the very least, what the show has become.
